cs.NE, cs.MS, cs.CE, cs.BM, cs.CM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a mathematical model for electrodiffusion in neural tissue and studies ephaptic coupling in an unmyelinated axon bundle. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper introduces a new finite element-based numerical scheme for the KNP-EMI model. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper discusses a mathematical model for ion concentrations in a geometrically-explicit representation of the intra- and extracellular domains. 
- cs.BM (Biomolecules and Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the effect of altered ion concentrations on the electrical potentials in excitable cells. 
- cs.CM (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of finite element methods for handling geometries of arbitrary dimension and arbitrary polynomial degree.
